  "original_title": "CCPI-based headline inflation hits 60.8% in July",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "CCPI-based headline inflation hits 60.8% in July",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Headline inflation of Sri Lanka, as measured by the year-on-year (Y-o-Y) change in the Colombo Consumer Price Index (CCPI, 2013=100) increased to 60.8% in July 2022 from 54.6% in June 2022.",
        "This increase in Y-o-Y inflation was driven by the monthly increases of both Food and Non-Food categories.",
        "Accordingly, Food inflation (Y-o-Y) increased to 90.9% in July 2022 from 80.1% in June 2022, while Non-Food inflation (Y-o-Y) increased to 46.5% in June 2022 from 42.4% in June 2022."
      ],
